Tobacco

Company Overview of North Atlantic Trading Company, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Thomas F. Helms Jr.Executive Chairman, North Atlantic Trading Company, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships77--
Background

		Mr. Thomas F. Helms Jr., has been the Chief Executive Officer and the President of NTC since 1988. Mr. Helms has been Chief Executive Officer of National Tobacco Finance Corporation since 1988 and previously served as its President since 1988. He serves as the President of North Atlantic Cigarette Company, Inc. (“NACC“). Mr. Helms serves as Chairman and President of Stoker and Fred Stoker & Sons, Inc. and RBJ Sales, Inc. He serves as Chairman of the Board of Directors, ... President and Chief Executive Officer of North Atlantic Operating Company, Inc. (“NAOC“). He has been an Executive Chairman of North Atlantic Trading Co Inc. since June 1997. He serves as the Executive Chairman of Intrepid Brands LLC. He served as the President of Turning Point. Mr. Helms served with International Flavors & Technology, Inc., a wholly owned non-operating subsidiary of North Atlantic Trading Company Inc., since October 1997. Mr. Helms served as the President of North Atlantic Trading Co Inc. from January 19, 2005 to June 10, 2005 and served as its Chief Executive Officer from June 1997 to June 10, 2005. Mr. Helms also served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Culbro Corporation's smokeless tobacco division from 1983 to March 1986. From 1979 to 1982, Mr. Helms served as General Manager of the Etherea Cosmetics and Designer Fragrances Division of Revlon, Inc. He served in marketing and sales positions in various divisions of Revlon Consumer Products Corporation. Mr. Helms served as the Chief Executive Officer of North Atlantic Holding Company Inc. from June 1997 to April 2005 and served as its President from January 19, 2005 to April 2005. He has been the Non-Executive Chairman of Turning Point Brands, Inc. (formerly North Atlantic Holding Company Inc.) since May 2016. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of National Tobacco Company, L.P. He serves as Chairman of National Tobacco Finance Corporation. He served as Executive Chairman of Turning Point Brands, Inc. from May 2006 to May 2016 and served as its Non-Executive Chairman from June 1997 to May 2006. He has been a Director of Standard Diversified Opportunities Inc. since June 2017. He has been a Director of Turning Point Brands, Inc. ("Turning Point") (formerly North Atlantic Holding Company, Inc.) since 1997. He serves as a Director of North Atlantic Trading Company, Inc. Mr. Helms serves as a Director of Stoker and Director of Fred Stoker & Sons, Inc. and RBJ Sales, Inc. He serves as a Director of North Atlantic Cigarette Company, Inc. (“NACC“).Read Full Background




